## Priority Order
1. Critical bugs (BUG-XXX) from @000-variables.mdc[backlog]
2. In-progress items from @000-variables.mdc[changelog]
3. Tasks with "Has Issues" status in @000-variables.mdc[implementation_steps] or @000-variables.mdc[current_state]
4. High priority features from @000-variables.mdc[backlog]
5. Tasks with a status of "Not Started" in @000-variables.mdc[implementation_steps]

Before making any code changes **follow this exact sequence**:

1. **Perform maintenance tasks:**
   - Check current system datetime
   - Move items older than 24 hours from "Completed Today" to "Recent Completions" in @000-variables.mdc[changelog]
   - Move items older than 7 days to @000-variables.mdc[changelog_archive]
   - Update timestamps in all document headers

2. **Review @000-variables.mdc[current_state]** to understand the project status
   - Focus on "Current Focus Areas"
   - Note any "Known Issues" 
   - Check "Recent Accomplishments"

3. **Review @000-variables.mdc[backlog]** for highest priority items
   - Critical bugs MUST be addressed before any new features
   - Recently added items should be reviewed for priority
   - Items matching current focus areas take precedence

4. **Check @000-variables.mdc[changelog]** for in-progress work
   - Continue any "In Progress" items before starting new work
   - Review recent completions to avoid duplicating work

5. **Review @000-variables.mdc[implementation_steps]** to understand the project plan
   - Identify the current implementation phase
   - Check dependencies for potential tasks
   - Verify task priorities and sequences

6. **Select the next task based on the priority order above**
   - Report your understanding of the current state to the user
   - Explain which task you're planning to work on and why
   - List any dependencies for that task and confirm they're completed
   - Move the selected item from backlog to "In Progress" in changelog if it's a new task

7. Examine the code base
8. Begin editing and testing code for the **chosen task**
9. **Update task documentation** as you work:
   - Add current system datetime
   - Add implementation notes to the backlog entry
   - Document issues encountered and solutions
   - List all files modified with explanations
   - Record test results

10. **Upon completion**:
    - Move the item to "Completed Today" in @000-variables.mdc[changelog]
    - Update status in @000-variables.mdc[backlog] and @000-variables.mdc[implementation_steps]
    - Add any new issues discovered to @000-variables.mdc[backlog]
    - Update relevant sections in @000-variables.mdc[current_state]

# Changelog Maintenance Guidelines

Every time you start a new session:

1. Check for items older than 7 days in the "Recent Completions" section of @000-variables.mdc[changelog]
2. Move these items to @000-variables.mdc[changelog_archive] under the appropriate month section
3. Include the full item detail including ID, title, completion date, and implementation notes
4. Maintain chronological order within each month section
5. Create a new month section if needed

# Status-first protocol

When receiving any new instructions, **first check how they align with the current state tracking before proceeding**.

# Verification checkpoint

⚠️ After reviewing the implementation files but before exploring any code:
- You **MUST** report your understanding of the current state
- You **MUST** explain which task you're planning to work on and why
- You **MUST** list any dependencies for that task and confirm they're completed